content:
RICHARDSON, Wendy
Presently a first year graduate student at Baylor College of Medicine with
Costas studying expression of the sea urchin gene. Worked
previously for a Masters degree with Stephen Benson (Cal State, Hayward) on
expression of the embryonic spicule matrix gene of sea urchin.
SMITH, Susan
First year graduate student at Rensselaer Polytechnic in plant developmental
biology. Worked previous in industry for three years as a biologist at the
Sandoz Crop Protection Corp. Will probably be doing a plant embryogenesis
thesis in relation to flowering. Wants broad background in animal systems of
development.
TANAKA, Elly
First year graduate student at UCSF. Has some background in Drosophila and
nematode genetics. Presently interested in problems of early develop ent and
might do thesis on mechanisms of establishing early polarity in embryos.
Recommended by Timothy Mitchison and Kenyon. 
TILLINGHAST, Henry 
An Associate Professor of Biology at the US Air Force Academy. Has a from
Oxford (1985), with a thesis on cell communication during aggregation and
development in slime mold. Will soon have completed his required years in the
Air Force and plans a research oriented career thereafter.
WATSON, Kellie 
A Canadian student at UC Irvine since 1987, with a Masters degree (Kansas)
after having previously studied Drosophila melanotic tumor genetics. Working
presently on a thesis with Peter Bryant studying growth-control mutants.
WICKRAMASINGHE, Dineli
A Ceylonese (BA Mount Holyoke) graduate student since 1986 at Tufts University
School of Medicine. Working in David Albertini's lab on molecular and
structural problems associated with the acquisition of meiotic competence in
mouse oocytes.
ZAHNER, Joseph
A first year graduate student in Developmental Biology at Johns Hopkins where
he did laboratory rotations during his first year but has not yet selected a
thesis problem. Is interested in molecular aspects of development. Here for
the diversity of exposure. Recom ended by William Busa and Chris Cheney.
